  "name": "Morrison COU1 — ML-augmented CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for a machine-learning surrogate model that predicts pump-induced hemolysis indices for the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The ML model (a gradient-boosted regressor) was trained on CFD-derived shear-stress histories and experimental RH measurements from a single laboratory campaign; it replaces direct CFD integration for rapid tolerance-sensitivity sweeps. COU1 evaluates whether the surrogate can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. All 13 ASME V&V 40 factors are addressed; validation results are drawn exclusively from held-out splits of the original training distribution. One out-of-distribution pump geometry was evaluated post hoc and the model was reported to 'generalize well,' but no systematic covariate-shift study, noise-injection experiment, or adversarial perturbation analysis was conducted or linked.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-ml-hemo-req-001",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-ml-hemo-claim-001",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-gbr-hemolysis-surrogate-v2",
