      "name": "Held-out test-set RH prediction accuracy",
      "description": "The gradient-boosted surrogate was evaluated on a randomly partitioned 20% hold-out split of the 1,240-sample CFD/experimental dataset used for training. Mean absolute error in RH was 0.031 (95% CI: 0.027–0.035); R² = 0.961. All test samples were drawn from the same five flow-speed operating points and the same pump geometry family as the training corpus. No stratification by geometric outlier or flow-regime boundary was applied.",
